                    {
                        xtype: 'container',
                        html: '<p>It seems strange today to think that you could swim here in the lake but right up until the 1980’s the Green Lake was an important local amenity for Cavan Town with swimming, fishing, horse riding and even skating being held here.  </p> <p>In fact in the winter of 1947, the coldest winter ever recorded in Ireland, it was said that the ice was so thick, reported to be two feet in depth, cars could be driven on the lake and many locals were skating constantly on the surface.  </p> <p>Moving on to our boardwalk we cross the floodplains with ease.  Again made from recycled plastic, the reason being that this plastic, apart from being a reusable material, is hard wearing, low maintenance and above all not slippy. </p> <p>One of the main features here at the lake is that it is accessible to all and even the paths are designed so that the gradients are accessible to wheelchair users. Take a look at our information boards showing our native animals living here at the Green Lake.</p>',
                        id: 'htmlPoint6',
                        styleHtmlContent: true,
                        scrollable: true
                    }
